You ran the command wsl --install -d Ubuntu in your Git Bash terminal, which initiated the installation of a native Ubuntu Linux distribution integrated directly into Windows via WSL 2.
Automatic Mount: The Linux environment automatically mounted your Windows C: drive under the path /mnt/c/. This is why, when the Ubuntu shell launched, you were immediately placed inside your Windows project directory:
Action,Command,Notes
Launch Ubuntu,wsl or wsl -d Ubuntu,"Run this from your Windows Command Prompt, PowerShell, or Git Bash."
Launch and Run Specific Command,wsl ubuntu ls -a,Runs a command inside Ubuntu without opening the full shell.
Exit Ubuntu,exit,Closes the current Ubuntu shell session.
Check WSL Status,wsl -l -v,Shows all installed distributions and their running state.

